snippet.textDisplay: As someone who used to do the "fat" shaming thing when I was younger (and infinitely stupider), I know that people who bully people about their weight because of "concern" for their health are usually not concerned (as weight is generally a poor indicator of general health, you can't know their daily habits, blood test numbers, HR and BP just by looking at someone). They actually want to point out what they perceive as flaws in others because they're deeply insecure themselves. I had an eating disorder and I have not liked my body for most of my life, so fat shaming was a way to be like "I'm better than you". Bottom line, if you're shaming others for things about their appearance that they might not be able to control (as it's not easy for everyone to control their weight even if they work their asses off and have better habits than the person throwing insults), you're not better than them, you're worse because you look like a petty asshole, and that is something you can control, you just choose not to.
